-- Copasa Second-Quarter Net Income Falls 29% to 76.2 Million Reais
-- B y   H e l d e r   M a r i n h o
-- 2013-08-07T01:29:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-07/copasa-second-quarter-net-income-falls-29-to-76-2-million-reais.html
Cia. de Saneamento de Minas Gerais,
 Brazil ’s second-biggest water utility by market value, said
second-quarter profit fell to 76.2 million reais from 107.1
million reais a year earlier.  Net income adjusted was estimated at 122.6 million reais,
according to analysts’ estimates compiled by Bloomberg.  Sales rose 15 percent from a year earlier to 949.8 million
reais, the company known as Copasa said in a regulatory filing.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Helder Marinho at 
 hmarinho@bloomberg.net  